OL,3,CFamilies remember Dunblane victims on
OL,4,C30th anniversary of school shooting
OL,6,F"But I'm coming to a point in my life,
OL,7,Fwhere I feel like I should step back a
OL,8,Fbit and know that there are others who
OL,9,Fwant to continue."
OL,11,FAfter the tragedy, there was an
OL,12,Foutpouring of support received by the
OL,13,Ftown of Dunblane in 1996.
OL,15,FPeople sent cards, letters, and gifts
OL,16,Ffrom around the world: strangers
OL,17,Frallying behind a town in grief to
OL,18,Fextend an invisible hand and hold on.
