OL,3,CFamilies remember Dunblane victims on
OL,4,C30th anniversary of school shooting
OL,6,FMother's Day cards, sent to the
OL,7,Fmothers who would miss out, took place
OL,8,Fjust days after the tragedy. And many
OL,9,Fof the messages sent with floral
OL,10,Ftributes have been saved and stored at
OL,11,FThe Dunblane Centre.
OL,13,FThese were meaningful tokens for the
OL,14,Ffamilies who suffered loss, a sign of
OL,15,Fgood trying to triumph over
OL,16,Funspeakable evil, but most of the
OL,17,Fitems have disappeared from the public
OL,18,Feye and have been kept in storage
OL,19,Fsince.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
